          <change when="2021-02-25T09:10:54-05:00"
                 who="http://papyri.info/editor/users/james.cowey">Vote - Accept-Straight-to-Finalization - The reading is clearly correct. The reading π̣[έ]πεισο̣μα̣ι̣ was introduced by P.Giss.Apoll. 16 and appears not to have been commented on in the Berichtigungsliste. The reading in P.Giss. I 78 was indeed πέπεισμαι. I think there is little point in preserving the reading of the non existent form posited by P.Giss.Apoll. 16. The explanations in the editorial history is surely enough. Lin4 should simply be encoded 4. ἐνεργήσασα. πέπεισμαι ὅτι [.2]ν̣ευν σ̣ου [ἀπέ]</change>
          <change when="2021-02-25T08:30:30-05:00"
                 who="http://papyri.info/editor/users/Mike%20Sampson">Vote - AcceptText - Yes, agreed.</change>
          <change when="2021-02-25T07:32:37-05:00"
                 who="http://papyri.info/editor/users/nikos">Commit - l. 4 π̣[έ]πεισο̣μα̣ι̣ -&gt; πέπεισμαι. On photo. The reading is more than clear (all letters are there and there is no need for underdots). In any way the form π̣[έ]πεισο̣μα̣ι̣ does not exist. πέπεισμαι is perfect tense of πείθομαι.</change>
